<subSubSection id="F0BA5496072609DD49ADFC700A75859E" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4F77C4DEE4C660080131A6FEAFA4BEF7" pageNumber="91">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9067D0857D78308EB01D75CFAA66CA84" lastPageNumber="92" pageNumber="91">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="09994A79A4A031F3C8052EB1C5DB8374" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E8C46024-6826-43CD-8E24-EB5720507DCA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys picturatus Costa 2000:12" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="picturatus">S. picturatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="67636CC6870474AA567117AAAE785194" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C9AAD97D-723E-4D4F-A297-1F8ED1AA0D29" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys carlettoi Costa &amp; Nielsen 2004:126" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="carlettoi">S. carlettoi</taxonomicName>
and distinguished from all other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="8670B8581843A942B6F87D6B5F3896C4" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnificus">S. magnificus</taxonomicName>
group by having pectoral fins red in males (vs. hyaline). Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="273A8D4FFCF2946E5962F0CF6DF3B0CC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E8C46024-6826-43CD-8E24-EB5720507DCA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys picturatus Costa 2000:12" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="picturatus">S. picturatus</taxonomicName>
and distinguished from remaining species of the 
<taxonomicName id="C003C8F4867DCDDC80B028746BF24C76" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnificus">S. magnificus</taxonomicName>
group by possessing distal border of the unpaired fins black in males (vs. never a black border), dorsal and anal fins rounded in males and without filamentous rays in males (vs. pointed, with filamentous rays on the tip); differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F238F62E95AC26E2201FB35FCFB90710" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E8C46024-6826-43CD-8E24-EB5720507DCA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys picturatus Costa 2000:12" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="picturatus">S. picturatus</taxonomicName>
in having five to seven red bars on anterior portion of 
<pageStartToken id="684FDD9D78E755FE3B1EE9C01CFF9B2C" pageNumber="92">flank</pageStartToken>
in males (vs. eight to ten), 13-15 bars on flank in females (vs. 18-20), and greenish blue vermiculate transverse stripes on unpaired fins in males (vs. greenish blue dots).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
